         <abstract>
            <p>How well an accounting system deals with inflation depends on the answers to two questions: Which unit of measurement does it use -- nominal dollars or constant dollars? What method of evaluation does it use -- acquisition cost or replacement value? Specific Price Level Accounting, which incorporates both specific replacement values and adjustments for changes in the general price level, is particularly useful for funds flow analysis.</p>
          </abstract>
